Send us your comments and feedback
Thank you for your feedback. Please keep the current subject line if your comment relates to this topic.
Copy and share link to current indicator
Create a custom region with selection
Hold the SHIFT key to select multiple regions
Display multiple indicators in the line graph for the selected map area
Paste data in the following box (CTRL + V)
Go to Excel and select - Edit -> Paste. You can also paste the data in a text editor such as Notepad; save the file with the extension .html and open the file in a Web Browser.
File format .CSV (can be opened by most spreadsheets and database software)
Convert axis to use a log scale
Convert axis to use a linear scale
Selected indicators have no dates in common

Please adjust the sliders in the order from top to bottom (first indicator to last indicator). Weights for indicators above the current one remain fixed. Weights for indicators below will automatically adjust to ensure they add up to 100%.
Move text labels or map points
Stop moving text labels or map points
Create and copy index of links (HTML)
Double-click to open the RSS feed.
Select all within this data range
Select a time-period or play animation over time
Click on a country in the country list to select it
Touch a map area to display an info popup. Move the map by dragging it with your finger. To zoom, touch an area with two fingers at once and spread them apart.

Different graph types can be selected above. Touch a country label to display data for that country. To zoom in, touch an area with two fingers and spread them apart, then drag with both fingers to move the graph.
Select one of the following menu options
This is the category & indicator selection panel. Click on the star icon to bookmark the selected indicator.
This panel shows the bookmarked indicator. It is the x-axis variable if the scatterplot graph is selected.

Select any indicators from the list on the left-hand side to create a composite indicator. Click on a selected indicator on the right-hand side for more options. Then optionally give your composite indicator a name and click on 'Create composite indicator'.
In this panel you can select the graph type. You can also customize the graph and change the x and y axis values.
Click on any of the colors or values to change the map colors or values ranges.
This panel shows the values represented by symbols of various sizes.
This panel displays information related to the currently selected indicator

This table displays the data for the currently selected indicator, as well as the bookmarked indicator - if any. In addition, data for all indicators in the current category and/or for the whole time series can also be shown.
Click to select or deselect an item. To narrow down to the selection, click on the 'select' button.
This panel contains various options to customize the graph and the map, such as colors and text size.
This panel enables you to customize the map colors. Select a 'diverging' color scheme to emphasize both high and low values.
Export the selected indicator either as a map, graph or table.
This panel provides links to publications relevant to the selected country.
